-1303651724.text: "Phosphorylation of GSK3beta at serine 9 inactivates this kinase activity and causes stabilization and nuclear localization of beta-catenin from the plasma membrane to the cytoplasm and the nucleus, where the latter acts as a transcription cofactor for developmentally regulated genes."
